{"cursor":"50594","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"]]\n\n in Mexico]] in Brazil]] and zebras in the Masai Mara park reserve in Kenya.]]\n , Poland]]\n\n'Ecotourism' is a form of tourism involving visiting fragile, pristine, and\nrelatively undisturbed natural areas, intended as a low-impact and often small\nscale alternative to standard commercial (mass) tourism. Its purpose may be to\neducate the traveler, to provide funds for ecological conservation, to directly\nbenefit the economic development and political empowerment of local communities,\nor to foster respect for different cultures and for human rights. Since the\n1980s ecotourism has been considered a critical endeavour by environmentalists,\nso that future generations may experience destinations relatively untouched by\nhuman intervention. {{cite book\n | last = Honey first = Martha year = 2008 title = 'Ecotourism and\n | Sustainable Development: Who Owns Paradise?' edition = Second publisher =\n | Island Press location = Washington, DC id = ISBN 1-59726-125-4 ISBN 978-\n | 1597261258 page = 33\n}} Several university programs use this description as the working\ndefinition of ecotourism. Untamed Path\n[http://www.untamedpath.com/Ecotourism/defining.html Defining Ecotourism].\nRetrieved on 2009-03-24.\n\nGenerally, ecotourism deals with living parts of the natural environments. Sadry, B.N (2009)\" Fundamentals of Geotourism: with a special\nemphasis on Iran\", Samt Organization publishers, Tehran.220p. (English Summary\navailable Online at: http://physio-geo.revues.org/3159?file=1 Ecotourism\nfocuses on socially responsible travel, personal growth, and environmental\nsustainability. Ecotourism typically involves travel to destinations where\nflora, fauna, and cultural heritage are the primary attractions. Ecotourism is\nintended to offer tourists insight into the impact of human beings on the\nenvironment, and to foster a greater appreciation of our natural habitats.\n\nResponsible ecotourism includes programs that minimize the negative aspects of\nconventional tourism on the environment and enhance the cultural integrity of\nlocal people. Therefore, in addition to evaluating environmental and cultural\nfactors, an integral part of ecotourism is the promotion of recycling, energy\nefficiency, water conservation, and creation of economic opportunities for local\ncommunities. For these reasons, ecotourism often appeals to\nadvocates of environmental and social responsibility.\n","linknr":172,"url":"ecotourist","recorded":1372152473,"links":["//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Ecotourism","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Ecotourist&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#semi","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png","/wiki/File:Llano_del_Muerto_in_Perquin_El_Salvador.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Llano_del_Muerto_in_Perquin_El_Salvador.jpg/220px-Llano_del_Muerto_in_Perquin_El_Salvador.jpg","/wiki/File:Llano_del_Muerto_in_Perquin_El_Salvador.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf6/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/wiki/El_Salvador","/wiki/File:Cedar_of_lebanon_003.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/